text="Being n-truncated is a proposition › "><fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001P.xml"
title="Being n-truncated is a proposition"
addr="//erct/erct-001P"
type="local">Being <fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001G.xml"
title="n-truncated type"
addr="//erct/erct-001G"
type="local"><html:span
style="white-space: nowrap"
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:link> is a <fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="//erct/erct-001I"
type="local">proposition</fr:link></fr:link> › </fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>We proceed by induction on the <fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001F.xml"
title="Indexing of truncation levels"
addr="//erct/erct-001F"
type="local">truncation level</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
  <fr:ol><fr:li>When <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n=-2]]></fr:tex>, we recall from <fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001N.xml"
title="Being contractible is a proposition"
addr="//erct/erct-001N"
type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number
addr="//erct/erct-001N" /></fr:link> that being <fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001H.xml"
title="Contractible type"
addr="//erct/erct-001H"
type="local">contractible</fr:link> is a <fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="//erct/erct-001I"
type="local">proposition</fr:link>.</fr:li>
    <fr:li>When <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n=-1]]></fr:tex>, we recall from <fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001O.xml"
title="Being a proposition is a proposition"
addr="//erct/erct-001O"
type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number
addr="//erct/erct-001O" /></fr:link> that
      being a <fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="//erct/erct-001I"
type="local">proposition</fr:link> is a <fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="//erct/erct-001I"
type="local">proposition</fr:link>.</fr:li>
    <fr:li>For <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n \geq  0]]></fr:tex>, we assume by induction that being <html:span
style="white-space: nowrap"
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n-1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> is a <fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="//erct/erct-001I"
type="local">proposition</fr:link> to prove that being <html:span
style="white-space: nowrap"
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> is a <fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="//erct/erct-001I"
type="local">proposition</fr:link>. In other words, we must show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,y:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}\mathsf {isTruncated}\,
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen n-1\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\,A]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="//erct/erct-001I"
type="local">proposition</fr:link>. By our inductive hypothesis, this is a dependent product of <fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="//erct/erct-001I"
type="local">propositions</fr:link> (<fr:link
href="foreign-erct-erct-001B.xml"
title="Dependent product of propositions"
